                    <span>wonderful, and entertaining. couldn't put the book down. <BR>can't wait for the next book</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Joe Mantegna makes this CD shine</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
                      /
                      <span>4</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-06-16</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I loved this book, almost entirely due to Joe Mantegna's reading and characterization. Parker does a good job of telling us yet another Spenser story -- most of us don't read Spenser novels for the plot but for just how Parker write Spenser -- funny, sarcastic, wonderful. Mantegna does a fabulous job of bringing all of these characters to life. Go listen to it. It's wonderful.</span>
                  
              
